Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{4}(cut into 1/2-inch-thick wedges). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Mince a few slices until you have @onion{2%tbsp}(minced) for the meatloaf.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, gently combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, minced onion, half the @ketchup{1%unit}, salt (we used @salt{1/2%tsp}; 1 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper.

Form beef mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4 servings); place on a second #baking sheet{}. Brush tops of meatloaves with remaining ketchup.

Roast on middle rack until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

== Caramelized Onion ==

While potatoes and meatloaves cook, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large, preferably nonstick, pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1%tsp} and a splash of water. Cook, adding more splashes of water as necessary, until onion is caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer onion to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Horseradish Dijonnaise ==

While bread toasts, in a second small bowl, combine @creamy horseradish sauce{1%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, and half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}. Set aside.

== Assembly ==

Heat @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium heat. Add @sourdough bread{4%slices} and toast until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} per side (add more butter and work in batches as needed).

Lay toasted bread out on a #cutting board{}. Top half the bread slices with caramelized onion; spread remaining bread slices with sauce (save some for serving).

Cut each meatloaf crosswise into four slices; fan out slices over bread topped with caramelized onion. Close sandwiches and cut in half.

Divide sandwiches and potato wedges between plates. Serve with remaining sauce on the side for dipping.